Ansible tags:
we use ansible tags for executing or skipping specific tasks from playbook. 
first, write "tags: (task name) after every tasks in the indentation of module. Then during running playbook write ansible-playbook --tags (tag name) same as...
To skip a task write --skip-tags (tag name)
Ansible variables:
To edit specific word repitively in the playbook. 
syntax: ( for example)
hosts:
  hosts: all
  vars:
    - app: httpd
  tasks:
    - name: installl a package
      yum:
        name: "{{ app }}"
        state: latest
    - name: enable a service
      service:
        name: "{{ app }}"
        state: started
Ansible loop:
for repetition of a task (for example)
---
- name: file playbook
  hosts: all
  tasks:
    - name: creatingg a file
      file:
        path: "{{ item }}"
        state: touch
      loop:
        - /tmp/file1
        - /tmp/file2
        - /tmp/file3
Ansible vault:
Lock the playbook
first create playbook " ansible-vault create (playbook name)", put password, now if you cat it, it will not show the playbook data 
for edit write "ansible-vault edit (playbook name)"
If you want to read playbook write " ansible-vault decrypt (playbook name)" and cat it.
